# Groundwork - Cursor Rules

This file provides guidance to Cursor AI when working with code in this repository.

## Project Overview

**Groundwork** — An agentic engineering toolkit template with documentation-driven development, persistent AI knowledge capture, and phase-based planning.

## Development Methodology

This project uses **Groundwork** — a documentation-driven approach:

1. **Read `docs/PRODUCTION_ROADMAP.md` first** — Single source of truth (Current Focus section at top)
2. **Check phase tasks** — `docs/phases/phaseN/PHASEN_TASKS.md` for detailed checkboxes
3. **Log decisions** — Add ADRs to `docs/DECISIONS.md` for significant choices
4. **Update progress** — Check boxes as tasks complete

### Key Documents
- `docs/CURRENT_FOCUS.md` — Active work context
- `docs/PRODUCTION_ROADMAP.md` — Single source of truth (Current Focus at top)
- `docs/DECISIONS.md` — Architectural Decision Records
- `docs/TECH_STACK.md` — Technology choices & versions
- `docs/ARCHITECTURE_GUIDE.md` — System design rationale
- `docs/COMMANDS.md` — AI commands reference

## Monorepo Structure

```
groundwork/
├── apps/
│   ├── web/                    # React 19 + Vite + Tailwind 4
│   └── api/                    # Hono API server
├── packages/
│   ├── shared/                 # Types, constants, utilities
│   └── ui/                     # UI component library
└── docs/                       # Documentation (roadmap, ADRs, phases)
    ├── PRODUCTION_ROADMAP.md   # Single source of truth
    ├── DECISIONS.md            # Architectural Decision Records
    ├── TECH_STACK.md           # Technology choices
    ├── ARCHITECTURE_GUIDE.md   # System design rationale
    └── phases/                 # Phase-based task planning
```

## Tech Stack

**Frontend:** React 19.x, TypeScript, Vite 6.x, Tailwind CSS 4.x
**Backend:** Node.js 22+, Hono 4.x
**Infrastructure:** pnpm workspaces, Turborepo

## Commands

```bash
pnpm dev              # Run all packages
pnpm build            # Build all
pnpm lint             # Linting
pnpm typecheck        # Type checking
```

## Coding Preferences

- Clean architectures, modular approach
- Tailwind for styling
- Latest stable versions
- Avoid unnecessary duplications
- Keep consistency across the codebase

## Available Prompts

See `.cursor/prompts/` for reusable prompts:
- `start-session.md` — Load project context at session start
- `log-decision.md` — Create an ADR
- `plan-phase.md` — Generate a new phase task document
- `update-focus.md` — Update Current Focus section
- `check-task.md` — Mark tasks as complete
- `phase-status.md` — Show phase progress
- `cleanup.md` — Reset to template state
